So, although I knew in advance we were going to be keep a few elite Russian hockey players (yes, yes, I understand that my life is much weirder than many people's.) in our guest room for a few weeks while they attend a nearby off-season training, I was a total idiot American and just assumed that they'd all speak English.The first one arrived an hour ago, and his first words were: "Sorry, I don't speak English."What do I do now? (I just down loaded Google Translate on my Android phone, and did my best for a quick "Welcome, here's your room, here's the bathroom, shower, etc.") I also SOS's my friend who claimed to speak Russian, but when he arrived he admitted to just knowing a very few rudimentary phrases, so I've got nobody local that I know who knows Russian.I need to learn some Russian, fast. . .
Semi On
