Posted: Thu Mar 15, 2012 10:01 pm
chalex wrote:Sounds like you could have a computer in the common room with Google Translate open on it. All the time.Do that. But you'll need to install the Cyrillic keyboard (Russian layout) on your computer. The traditional Russian layout has nothing whatever to do with the Qwerty layout, and that's probably what they'll be used to. If they can touch-type you won't even need stickers. Otherwise, you could get a Cyrillic sticker set for the keyboard, and you should have no trouble communicating, albeit slowly. I can't imagine you'll be able to learn enough Russian in a short amount of time to be able to say or understand much more than, "Hello," "Goodbye," and, "And now, I am to drink with the guy who send the dogs at the local residents in Zambia. This is not stair related. A monkey is on the table."
Last edited by naphini on Thu Mar 15, 2012 10:07 pm
